text: Not-so-crowded Food court I like having breakfast at. Fry Prawn Mee stall has very good Prawn Mee, Hokkien Mee, Satay Bee Hoon and Laksa. No doubt a bit pricey but I alway finish the food. Value-for-money.

Value for money hokkien prawn mee! $5 big plate with generous prawns, sotong! Though noodle is a bit dry, would be awesome if its more wet. Personal preference i guess. Overall, $5 good deal for such a big plate!

Came to try the satay Bee hoon which is available only for morning and lunch. Instead try the fried hokkien mee and it's quite good, a bit of wok hei and instead of sotong it's baby squid. Will come again to try the satay bee hoon and laksa üëçüòä
Hokkien prawn noodle is good! Big fresh prawns and only $5!
Big and airy coffeeshop, however as of Jul 2023 many stores have closed down. There is only caifan, banmian fish soup, 2 halal stores, zichar and a drink store now.
